      {
        "id": "Observation.component:feeding.value[x]",
        "path": "Observation.component.value[x]",
        "short": "Feeding",
        "definition": "Feeding indicates the extent to which a patient is capable of eating independently. \r\n\r\nIn this scale, the following interpretations are used:\r\n\r\n*  Not independent: not capable of eating independently.\r\n*  Help: food is purÃ©ed; patient does feed themselves, but needs help cutting food, spreading butter, et cetera.\r\n*  Independent: capable of eating normal food (including hard food). The food can be cooked and served by others, but is not to be purÃ©ed.",
        "alias": [
          "Eten"
